Slide 3:
What is a Digital Wallet?

Slide 4:
What is a Digital Wallet?
•	A digital wallet, also known as an “e-Wallet,” is an electronic device or online service that allows a consumer to make electronic transactions.
•	The most commonly used digital wallets are:
	ApplePay
	Google Pay
	Samsung Pay
Other types of Digital Wallets include Fitbit Pay, Garmin Pay, Masterpass by Mastercard, Visa Checkout, and more.

Slide 5:
Supported Devices
•	The Shift4 gateway supports Digital Wallet transactions on a number of devices:
Ingenico
-	iPP320, iPP350, iSMP4*, iSC Touch 250, and iSC Touch 480
Verifone***
	MX 915, MX 925
Equinox**
	L5200, 15300
*iSMP4 support does not include Google Pay.
**Devices require specific DUKPT keys for encryption.
***Verifone devices do not support Level 3 data.

Slide 6:

Digital Wallets
Transaction Flow

Slide 7:
Digital Wallet Transaction Flow

1.  Customer presents phone/payment
    method to reader.
2.  Transaction data passed to Shift4
    securely for processing.
3.  Shift4 receives response from
    processor and passes back to device.
   Receipt
4.  Receipt is printed by the device and phone may
    beep to alert payment completion

Slide 8:
Shift4’s Digital Wallet Features

Slide 9:
Shift4’s Digital Wallet Features
•	Digital Wallet transactions are processed just like a regular credit or debit card transaction.
•	The POS automatically detects the transaction as a digital wallet transaction and passes it to Shift4.
•	Digital Wallet transactions are routed to the appropriate processor and sent to the card brands in the same manner as a regular transaction.
•	Digital Wallet transactions can be voided and refunded just like a regular transaction.
•	Tokenization can be manually enabled for Digital Wallet transactions.

Slide 10:
Reporting and Analytics

Slide 11:

Reporting & Analytics: Transaction Lookup
•	ITSA includes a “DigitalWallet” column to sort by digital wallet transactions performed by your merchant locations.

Slide 12:
Reporting & Analytics: Overview Report
•	The Overview Report will group Digital
Wallet transactions within the “Other”
card types on your reports.	

Slide 13:
Reporting & Analytics: Daily Volume
Report
•	Digital Wallet transactions are shown
under a specific transaction type on the Daily Volume Report.	

Slide 14:
Merchant Setup

Slide 15:
Merchant Setup
1.  Merchants must have NFC-enabled devices
   and an active Shift4 gateway account.
2.  The account must be enabled to use
    the correct device.
3.  Work with your Relationship Manager
    to run a test transaction

Slide 16:
Troubleshooting.

Slide 17:
Troubleshooting

Q: I swiped a Digital Wallet transaction. Why didn't
it process?

A:	Digital wallets are not intended to be used with
mag-stripe readers. Digital Wallet transactions must
be used for the payment device's contactless reader

Q: I have an NFC reader, but cannot see the
reporting
A:	The MID account might not be set up for
Digital Wallet. Contact your Relationship
Manager for more information
